subjective.chief_complaint: Generally unwell with sore throat and runny nose for 4-7 days
subjective.hpi: Patient presents with 4-7 day history of feeling generally unwell with sore throat, runny nose, fatigue, myalgia, and joint pain. Sore throat is improving. Has dry constant cough and nasal congestion. Reports night sweats for 4-7 days and fever initially which is settling with paracetamol/ibuprofen. Denies chest pain. Has shortness of breath on exertion. Reports generalized intermittent headaches without visual symptoms or photophobia. No nausea/vomiting, no bowel/urinary symptoms. Drinking fluids but has reduced appetite. No rashes.
subjective.patient_history: No significant past medical history. Family history: grandmother with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus. Social history: lives alone, works as accountant, occasional smoker/alcohol use, work is stressful, no mood symptoms.

plan.patient_instructions: Rest, push fluids, regular paracetamol/ibuprofen. Discussed red flag symptoms (shortness of breath, chest pain, fevers) - if present, urgent review with doctor required.
